<P>
MOVIES TO TAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Midnight (AMC Monday at 8 p.m.), a 1939 Mitchell Leisen film, was one of his 
best. It boasts a sophisticated, witty script by Billy Wilder and Charles 
Brackett, and stars Claudette Colbert as a chorine from the Bronx who arrives 
in Paris with only the striking gold lame gown on her back and 25 centimes in 
its matching purse. 
</P>
