<HEADLINE>
<P>
FASHION; SPOTS AND STRIPES FOREVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL EISENHOWER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Designers are seeing spots -- and stripes -- this season, providing a 
menagerie of leopard, zebra, tiger and other prints to choose from. Worn as 
accents or from head to toe, these second skins aren't intended for meek little 
lambs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA111394-0036 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 098053 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
November 13, 1994, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
