</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Sandy Masuo 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Queensryche, "Promised Land," EMI ***. Edgy, brooding, grand sonic gestures 
and gusts of harmonies continue to sweep over Queensryche's hard-rock 
terrain.But in the two years since their last album, they've tempered their 
songs, revealing some subtle new dynamics. "Promised Land" covers much 
territory, from stretches of introspection and social commentary to quiet 
acoustic moments and epic compositions. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent).  
