<HEADLINE>
<P>
ICONOGRAPHY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chico Marx isn't around, so I'll be the one to ask.I've been looking at the 
upper right-hand corner of Page 2 of the Sunday Calendar for months now, and 
I'd like to know: 
</P>
<P>
 Why a duck? 
</P>
<P>
 CARLO PANNO 
</P>
<P>
 Burbank 
</P>
<P>
 Editor's note: When I bought the redesign, the duck came with it.  
</P>
<P>
 I have been troubled by the picture of a skeleton head with a pencil in its 
mouth in the upper right-hand corner of the Letters page. 
</P>
<P>
 It seems to be a very dark and dismal picture for this section of the paper. 
What is the reason for it and can't you change it? 
</P>
<P>
 ROSEMARY C. WATSON 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
<P>
 Ditto for the pencil guy.  
</P>
<P>
 FEIFFER 
