<HEADLINE>
<P>
FAMILY STORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In "Say Howdy to Two Very Different Ranches" (July 17), Christopher Reynolds 
indicated that he wasn't sure when the Eatons bought their ranch.The ranch was 
previously owned by my great-uncle Austin Devol. My grandmother and Austin 
Devol's wife were sisters. 
</P>
<P>
 My grandfather was living in the Platte River Valley in southern Wyoming in 
1901-02 and lost his job when a mine closed. They moved up to Wolf Creek and my 
grandfather worked on the ranch until he heard there was work at a new smelter 
in Douglas, Ariz. I have my grandparent's diaries, plus a photograph of the big 
ranch house, which I can still see in the picture accompanying your article. 
</P>
<P>
 DAVID FROST 
</P>
<P>
 Phoenix 
</P>
