<HEADLINE>
<P>
CREDIT CAUTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 While driving in Italy this fall, we stopped at Hotel Grand Fasano, which you 
wrote about in July ("Lakeside Romances").We were surprised that this 
first-class hotel did not accept credit cards. We were short of cash and 
travelers checks, so we didn't stay. In times past, we always got by with 
credit cards. This time, stopping in other than major tourist spots, we found 
that one better have more than credit cards. Next time, more travelers checks 
and a PIN for the Visa for ATM use will be a priority.  
</P>
<P>
 CHARLES L. OLOBRI 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana 
