<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL FUNDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Re "A Fairer Deal on School Funds," editorial, Nov. 7: The Times is concerned 
that California gets a fair share of federal education dollars based on our 
growing number of disadvantaged students. 
</P>
<P>
 What about a fair share for all California kids? Whatever happened to the 
Serrano decision that mandated equal expenditures per student? Is this a battle 
that has already been lost? 
</P>
<P>
 The feds have been giving us extra money for disadvantaged kids for 30 years 
but their numbers keep growing. It's time to admit that money is not solving 
the problem. It's time to spend this money on all our kids. 
</P>
<P>
 BOB MUNSON 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park 
</P>
</TEXT>
