<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLF ROUNDUP; COUPLES-LOVE TEAM GOES FOR THREE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fred Couples and Davis Love III moved one round closer to knocking Jack 
Nicklaus and Arnold Palmer out of the record books at the World Cup of Golf. 
</P>
<P>
 Couples, who had a third-round 68, and Love, who shot 69, lost four strokes 
off their lead as the U.S. representative in the 32-country field at Dorado 
Beach, Puerto Rico, but it was still nine shots to second-place Zimbabwe. 
</P>
<P>
 Couples and Love were 34 under par after three trips around the Hyatt Dorado 
Beach east course. They are looking for their third consecutive title in the 
event and that would break their tie with Nicklaus and Palmer, who combined to 
win the title in 1962 and 1963. 
</P>
<P>
 Couples leads the individual competition at 20-under 196. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Jim Albus shot a six-under-par 66 and took a six-shot lead after three rounds 
of the season-ending Senior Tour Championship at Myrtle Beach, S.C. 
</P>
<P>
 Albus, 54, a former club pro who has led or shared the lead all the way, 
completed 54 holes in 201, 15 under par on the Dunes Club course. 
</P>
<P>
 Raymond Floyd shot 67 and is in second place at 207 in the $1.35-million 
tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
