<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP CROSS-COUNTRY; SANCHEZ WINS AT SECTION PRELIMINARIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT FARMER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley's Adalberto Sanchez is known for pushing the pace. 
</P>
<P>
 The senior's strategy worked to perfection Saturday, as he ran past a Division 
I-A field loaded with the area's top runners at the Southern Section 
cross-country preliminaries at Mt. San Antonio College. 
</P>
<P>
 Sanchez, the three-time South Coast League champion who won the county 
championship earlier this fall, cruised to the day's fastest time over the 
three-mile course in 15 minutes 8 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
 Newhall Hart's Brett Strahan (15:13) and Camarillo's Eleazar Hernandez (15:19) 
finished second and third; El Toro senior Martin Pennell (15:58) earned the 
final individual qualifying spot to next weekend's section final. 
</P>
<P>
 The Irvine girls' team, top-ranked in Orange County, breezed to an easy team 
victory in the second heat of the Division I-A. 
</P>
<P>
 Junior Jessica Corbin, who last week won the Sea View League title for the 
second year in a row, posted a 10-second victory over freshman Danielle Day of 
Quartz Hill in 18:33. 
</P>
<P>
 The Vaqueros advanced, scoring 67 points, edging Los Alamitos (73) and Dana 
Hills (88). 
</P>
<P>
 The second-ranked El Toro girls' team also advanced easily, finishing second 
(71 points) in the first heat of the Division I-A race. 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza won the second heat of Division I-AA with 37 points, behind an 18:12 
clocking from Courtney Pugmire. 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills (31 points), the South Coast League champion, and Aliso Niguel 
(66) advanced in Division II-AA; El Modena (38) and Santa Margarita (80) swept 
Division III-AA. Notes 
</P>
<P>
 The Newport Harbor and El Modena boys' teams each won their respective heats 
in the Division III-AA races. The Sailors edged Riverside Rubidoux, 45-59. The 
Vanquards outlasted La Habra 44-55. . . . Corona del Mar, led by a winning 
effort from senior Brian Slingsby (15:45), won the second heat of the Division 
III-A race. . . . Huntington Beach sophomores Tony Trueba (16:10) and Dan 
Gaston (16:26) advanced to the Division II final. . . . Mission Viejo edged 
Edison, 59-61, as the two leading qualifiers from the first heat of the 
Division II-A competition. . . . Brian Mitzel (16:10) and Daniel Gonzalez 
(16:16) finished third and fourth to lead Mater Dei, the county champion, to a 
team victory in the second heat of Division II-AA. . . . Katella (74 points), 
Laguna Hills (82) and Villa Park (84) advanced in the second heat of the 
Division II-A race. . . . The Edison girls' team, ranked third in the county, 
placed five runners among the top 10 to win the first heat of Division II-A. . 
. . Katie Nuanes of Santa Margarita (18:52) edged El Modena's Tara Whitfield 
(19:07) to win the first heat in Division III-AA. . . . Buena Park freshman 
Heather Garritson (18:31 in the second heat of Division III-AA) and Katella 
senior Jamie Vaicaro (19:10 in the second heat of Division II-A) were winners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
