<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP GIRLS' TENNIS PLAYOFFS; LOS ALAMITOS MAINTAINS EDGE, BEATS VILLA PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON CLIFFORD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Alamitos girls' tennis team has been winning when it's needed to all 
season. 
</P>
<P>
 The trend continued Saturday, when the third-seeded Griffins beat Villa Park, 
12-6, in the second round of the Southern Section Division II playoffs at Old 
Ranch Country Club in Seal Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 A strong performance by Los Alamitos' doubles teams proved to be the 
difference. The No. 1 team of Alison Miller and Michelle Schneider swept, 7-5, 
6-4, 6-2, and the No. 2 team of Laura Springosky and Sonia Ralli swept, 7-6 
(7-4), 6-2, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
 The upset over Villa Park's top doubles team of Jill Riley and Shawna Lerer 
clinched the match for the Griffins (19-1). Villa Park finishes 15-2. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm real proud of the doubles teams," Coach Debbie Fleming said. "We won two 
7-5 games and one 7-6 game. Those were huge for us." 
</P>
<P>
 The No. 3 doubles team of Gina Rozelle and Erin White also fared well, winning 
two of three matches, 6-7, 7-5, 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
 In singles, Villa Park's Faye DeVera dominated, sweeping her sets, 6-1, 6-0, 
6-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Fleming said No. 1 Melissa Rosenthal's victory over No. 2 Katey Becker was 
huge for the Griffins. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos next will face Los Angeles Marlborough in Tuesday's 
quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Division II matches: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 11, Redlands 7 -- Kelly Foster swept in singles, 6-3, 6-3, 6-3, and 
Susie Krum and Tami Demaree swept in doubles, 7-5, 6-3, 6-0, to lead Edison 
(14-6). Edison will face Laguna Beach in Tuesday's quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach 17, Marina 1 -- Amanda Hastings swept, 6-1, 6-0, 6-0, Lindsay 
Weiss won, 6-4, 6-1, 6-0, and Michelle Bray swept, 6-2, 6-0, 6-0, to lead 
Laguna Beach. Laguna Beach will face the winner of Edison-Redlands on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 In Division III: 
</P>
<P>
 El Dorado 10, Rosary 8 -- Linda Surapruik defeated Rosary's Karina Bolanos, 
6-1, in the last match to lead El Dorado (19-5) in a second-round victory. El 
Dorado will play the winner of Alhambra-Burbank in the third round. JON 
CLIFFORD 
</P>
</TEXT>
