<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP VOLLEYBALL ROUNDUP; SUNNY HILLS UPSETS ORANGE TO ADVANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By COREY LYONS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sunny Hills rallied and defeated previously unbeaten Orange, 14-16, 15-10, 
4-15, 15-12, 15-6, in the second round of the Southern Section Division II 
girls' volleyball playoffs Saturday at Orange High. 
</P>
<P>
 Tegan Catlin and Jennifer Coopman led the Lancers with 22 kills each. Sunny 
Hills plays Long Beach Poly in the next round. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers (17-1) jumped to an early lead in the fifth game and held on with 
Catlin's serve, which produced the final four points. 
</P>
<P>
 Charlene Conley led the Panthers with 23 kills. 
</P>
<P>
 Sunny Hills Coach Ron Kasser said his team prevailed with timely passing and 
clutch serving, elements he felt the Lancers lacked in the early going. 
</P>
<P>
 "We stress ball control, passing and defense, and we lost a lot of points 
early that we made up for in the end," Kasser said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers gained momentum in the fourth game, taking a 9-1 lead on Coopman's 
serve and Shannon Rosenkranz's four kills. After Orange climbed back into the 
game trailing, 14-12, Catlin responded with a hard sideline spike on Coopman's 
serve to even the match at two games. 
</P>
<P>
 Also in Division II: 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra 3, Foothill 1 -- Senior Kameron Shambeck had 28 kills and junior 
Jamie Ediger added 11 to lead La Habra (15-1), 12-15, 15-8, 15-6, 15-0. The 
Highlanders face Long Beach Millikan in the quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 In Division III: 
</P>
<P>
 Katella 3, Alta Loma 1 -- Kellie Alva had 23 kills and Rachel Nelson added 10 
kills to lead visiting Katella, 15-7, 15-11, 12-15, 15-11. The Knights (14-4) 
will face San Gabriel in the quarterfinals Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica 3, Etiwanda 2 -- Pacifica rallied from a two-games-to-one deficit to 
defeat Etiwanda, 11-15, 15-6, 11-15, 16-14, 15-10, and advanced to the 
quarterfinals to play Lake Arrowhead Rim of the World. Tracy Bunrs led the 
Mariners (15-2) with 23 kills and Cindy Vojtech had 13 kills. 
</P>
<P>
 In Division IV: 
</P>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel 3, El Centro Central Union 0 -- Sara Roberts and Jenny Roberts 
each had 10 kills to lead Calvary Chapel (14-4). The Eagles will play Tustin in 
the quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 In Division V: 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley Christian 3, Azusa 0 -- Jessica Olivier had 18 kills and 
Carmen Jusco added 14 for Capistrano Valley Christian (12-4), which swept, 
15-10, 15-7, 15-13, in the second round. Capistrano Valley Christian plays 
Sierra Madre Maranatha in the next round. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Margaret's 3, Cerritos Whitney 1 -- Emily Hallenceck had 20 kills, 
Stefanie Canright added 14 and Lisa Bevill had 49 assists for visiting St. 
Margaret's (11-5), which won, 15-13, 15-5, 13-15, 15-7. St. Margaret's will 
face Pasadena Mayfield in the quarterfinals Tuesday. COREY LYONS 
</P>
</TEXT>
