<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; TITANS GET FIRST VOLLEYBALL VICTORY OF SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cal State Fullerton women's volleyball team won its first match of the 
season Saturday night, beating host Utah State in four games. 
</P>
<P>
 The Titans' victory 17-15, 15-12, 15-8, 15-11, ended a 35-game losing streak 
that started last season. 
</P>
<P>
 Jennifer Lipski had 18 kills and Chelsea Wilhite added 16 for the Titans 
(1-25).  
</P>
<P>
 In another Big West match: 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach State 3, Pacific 2 -- Nichelle Burton had 23 kills to lead Long 
Beach State (22-4, 16-2) to the conference championship, 6-15, 15-6, 15-13, 
13-15, 15-12.  
</P>
<P>
 In the Mountain Pacific Sports Federation water polo tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 California 10, UC Irvine 9 -- Third-ranked Cal overcame a one-goal deficit in 
the fourth quarter and edged UCI (9-12). 
</P>
<P>
 In NCAA District 8 cross-country: 
</P>
<P>
 UCI men place seventh -- Bryan Contreras finished 26th in 32:33 to lead the 
Anteaters to a seventh-place finish in Tucson, Ariz. 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton was 12th and Long Beach State 13th. 
</P>
<P>
 The UCI women's team finished ninth and was led by Jo Jo Yaba, who was 33rd 
with a time of 18:48. The Titan women were 12th and the 49ers were 13th. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Rolex-ITA Southern California women's tennis regional: 
</P>
<P>
 Phebus stays alive -- Top-seeded Keri Phebus of UCLA, who played at Corona del 
Mar High, defeated seventh-seeded Isabela Petrov of Pepperdine, 6-3, 6-1, in 
the quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference swimming and diving: 
</P>
<P>
 UCI led by relay team -- The UC Irvine men's swim team defeated New Mexico 
State, 120-102.  
</P>
<P>
 The women's swim team fell to the Aggies, 140-95. 
</P>
<P>
 In the NAIA Far West Region women's volleyball playoffs: 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 3, The Master's 0 -- Celeste Young and Genevie 
Wright each had nine kills to lead fifth-seeded Southern California College, 
(18-10), 15-9, 15-12, 15-10, in the first round. 
</P>
