<P>
 Antelope Valley (2-7, 2-5) ended a four-game losing streak. 
</P>
<P>
 The Marauders' offense waited until its final home game to get on track. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley set season highs for points and yards gained with 382. 
</P>
<P>
 Roosevelt Miller gained 106 yards in 21 carries and Willy Spivey scored on 
runs of 20 and three yards. BRYAN RODGERS 
