<HEADLINE>
<P>
HANCOCK STIFLES GLENDALE, 27-24 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE BRESNAHAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After a 27-24 Western State Conference loss to Hancock College at Righetti 
High Saturday night, Glendale wasn't about to call the area inside the 
opponent's 20 the red zone. 
</P>
<P>
 It was more like the Dead Zone. 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale (4-5, 3-5 in WSC, 1-3 in division), clinging to a 14-7 lead in a 
North Division game, entered Hancock's red zone three times during the second 
quarter. But a blocked field goal, an interception and a fumble ended the 
threats. 
</P>
<P>
 Mark Powell of Hancock (6-3, 5-3, 3-1) set a school single-game record with 13 
catches for 196 yards, including a 35-yarder that set up the go-ahead touchdown 
with 5 minutes 18 seconds to play. 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale's Tony Delgado passed for 241 yards, but had three interceptions. 
MIKE BRESNAHAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
