<HEADLINE>
<P>
1 KILLED, 3 WOUNDED IN SEPARATE BOMB BLASTS IN BAGHDAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two bombs exploded in Baghdad on Saturday, killing a suspected bomber and 
wounding three students, state-run media reported. 
</P>
<P>
 The fatal bomb, containing up to 6 1/2 pounds of explosives, went off near the 
downtown Baghdad Hotel, the state-run Iraqi News Agency reported. 
</P>
<P>
 INA said the dead person was believed to be the bomber, but Baghdad radio 
reported that police were unable to identify the body because of the force of 
the explosion. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the fourth bombing in less than a month in the Iraqi capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
