 Twelve soldiers were executed by hanging and firing squad Saturday in the 
military government's first crackdown on renegade troops. 
</P>
<P>
 The soldiers, who ranged in rank from private to a 77-year-old warrant 
officer, were convicted in a military court of armed robbery, murder and other 
