<P>
PEDESTRIAN IS FATALLY STRUCK BY CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 50-year-old man was struck and killed Friday night while trying to dart 
across Newport Boulevard against a red light, investigators said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man, whose identity was withheld pending notification of his relatives, 
apparently ran in front of a car traveling north on Newport Boulevard at Bay 
Street and was struck about 7 p.m., Costa Mesa Officer Kelli Blanchard said 
Saturday.  
