CRASH INJURES WOMAN; WITNESSES SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police are seeking witnesses to a car crash late Thursday that left a woman 
seriously injured. 
</P>
<P>
 Linda Bloedel, 33, of Fullerton sustained multiple fractures and internal 
injuries when her late-model, silver Buick sedan was struck by a gray pickup 
truck about 11:30 p.m. Thursday at Harbor Boulevard and Orangethorpe Avenue, 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police arrested the driver of the pickup, 34-year-old Kelly Jenson of Anaheim, 
on suspicion of felony drunk driving. Jenson, who was not injured in the 
accident, is being held in the city's jail in lieu of posting $25,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
 Sgt. Hal Stevens said police received numerous calls reporting the incident, 
but none of the witnesses were still at the scene when officers arrived. "We 
would like to talk to anyone who saw the accident so we can establish what 
happened," Stevens said. 
</P>
