<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRASH VICTIM IN CRITICAL CONDITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 16-year-old girl was in extremely critical condition late Saturday after 
being struck by a hit-and-run driver while leaving a school homecoming dance, 
Burbank police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl was flown to Harbor-UCLA Medical Center after the accident Friday 
night.Her companion, a 16-year-old boy, was treated for a broken arm at 
Thompson Memorial Medical Center in Burbank and released, Burbank Police Lt. 
Van Miller said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police did not identify the two youths, but said the girl had just celebrated 
her birthday. 
</P>
<P>
 The couple was hit by a car traveling down the wrong side of the street after 
leaving the Glendale High School formal dance at the Castaway Restaurant, 1250 
Harvard Road, Miller said. 
</P>
<P>
 A vehicle described as a black or dark blue-gray, 1983 to 1987 Chevrolet 
Camaro was seen "speeding from the parking lot," Miller said. "Then a witness 
heard some screeching of tires, presumably from the accident." 
</P>
<P>
 After striking the young couple, the driver fled the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 According to the restaurant's director of catering, Rod Westmaas, the Castaway 
hosted three events Friday night: the homecoming dance with about 350 
teen-agers, a meeting of Armenian students from UCLA and a wedding party. 
</P>
<P>
 Police believe the driver was attending one of the events. 
</P>
<P>
 The Burbank Police Department is asking anyone with information about the 
accident to call (818) 953-8653. 
</P>
