<HEADLINE>
<P>
OBITUARY; FRED (SONIC) SMITH, 44; GUITARIST FOR BAND MC5 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fred (Sonic) Smith, original guitarist for the rock band MC5 and several other 
groups, including his Sonic's Rendezvous Band, has died. He was 44. 
</P>
<P>
 He died Nov. 4 of heart failure in Detroit, said his wife, Patti Smith, a poet 
and singer from the mid-1970s punk movement. 
</P>
<P>
 A native of West Virginia, the guitarist spent most of his life in Detroit. He 
began his career playing with local bands when he was a teen-ager and joined 
MC5 in the mid-1960s. The group pioneered the Detroit sound, a forerunner to 
heavy metal and punk rock. 
</P>
<P>
 Smith later made recordings with his wife, including the album "Dream of Life" 
in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to his wife, Smith is survived by a son, Jackson; a daughter, 
Jesse; his parents and two sisters, all of Detroit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
