<HEADLINE>
<P>
BISHOP'S MARRIAGE BOOK AROUSES INTEREST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A British bishop whose new book on marriage includes explicit advice about 
arousing your partner and making love around the house says he is amused by the 
interest it has generated. 
</P>
<P>
 "Our Flesh," the chapter on sex in the Rev. Michael Baughen's book, also 
describes orgasm as "an experience like no other" and recommends experiments 
with novel sexual positions. "After all, God meant us to enjoy sex. He made us 
the way we are and gave us the parts." 
</P>
<P>
 The 64-year-old Bishop of Chester and his wife, Myrtle, married for 38 years, 
wrote "Your Marriage" as a wide-ranging advice manual for couples. 
</P>
</TEXT>
