<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: VENTURA; 3 ARRESTED ON SUSPICION OF SHOOTING AT OFFICERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three suspected gang members were arrested early Saturday morning on suspicion 
of firing shots at Ventura police officers, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The officers were responding to a complaint about a group of youths standing 
on a corner in Cabrillo Village about 1:15 a.m. When the patrol car arrived, 
the youths ran from the area firing at the officers, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 While the officers took cover, the suspects jumped into a car and sped away, 
police said. Another patrol car located the fleeing suspects and stopped their 
car. The officers searched the car and found a handgun in the passenger side of 
the car, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Arrested on suspicion of assaulting a police officer with a deadly weapon were 
Edward Zizumbo, 21, and Ivan Flores, 19, both of Ventura. A 16-year-old Ventura 
boy was also arrested on the charge, police said. No motive was given for the 
assault. SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
