<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: EDUCATION: FUND DRIVE AT UNIVERSITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Loyola Marymount University is launching the first major comprehensive 
fund-raising campaign in its 83-year history to improve and expand its services 
to students and faculty. 
</P>
<P>
 The university has already raised about half of the $128 million needed to 
increase academic support services, student financial aid and facilities. 
</P>
<P>
 Said J. Terrence Lanni, chairman of the fund-raising campaign: "It is 
something that the university's alumni and friends say must be done to ensure 
that the university grows stronger and more visible as an institution of higher 
learning in this country." 
</P>
