<HEADLINE>
<P>
OREGON ABSENTEE VOTE GIVES GOP HOUSE SEAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Republicans picked up another seat in Oregon's five-member congressional 
delegation after absentee ballots were tallied, while another House race 
remained too close to call. 
</P>
<P>
 The absentee votes pushed state Sen. Jim Bunn past Democratic state Sen. 
Catherine Webber by 6,809 votes. The total was 117,106 votes for Bunn to 
110,297 for Webber. 
</P>
<P>
 That pulled Republicans even with Democrats in the delegation, with the 1st 
District race still undecided. 
</P>
</TEXT>
