</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana Valley could pull off some surprises this year under Stipp, the 
Falcons' first-year coach. With a few key victories, the Falcons could find 
themselves competing in the playoffs. Santa Ana Valley, El Modena and Villa 
Park should battle for the third and final automatic playoff berth. After a 
fourth-place finish last season, the Falcons return five lettermen, including 
three starters. Like most of the league, Santa Ana Valley is going to rely on 
guards to control the game. "Our weakness is that we need to learn how to win, 
especially in close, important games, " Stipp said. Defense is also going to 
play a big part in the Falcons' game plan, and Stipp thinks quickness is their 
main strength. Gibson and Lara are the only two seniors on the team, and their 
speed and ballhandling at guard will be one of the keys to Santa Ana Valley's 
success. Napier should also become a standout in the league this season. 
Although only a sophomore, at 6 feet 3 she should be able to handle the 
more-experienced post players around the league. SCHEDULE 
