Player, Bob Hope, golf trick-shot artist Dennis Walters and former PGA legal 
counsel Lloyd Lambert. . . . Nick Price has committed to playing in the 
$2.7-million Johnnie Walker World Championship in Jamaica, Dec. 15-18. 
</P>
<P>
 Final statistics show that Price won the player-of-the-year award by 128 
points over runner-up Mark McCumber and that Greg Norman won the Vardon Trophy 
for the lowest scoring average over second-place Price, 68.81 to 69.39. 
