<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEHLMAN SIGNS LETTER TO PLAY TENNIS AT ILLINOIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE DESMOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Harvard-Westlake High's Romy Mehlman has signed a national letter of intent to 
play tennis at the University of Illinois. 
</P>
<P>
 Mehlman, the Wolverines' No. 1 singles player, chose the Illini over 
Northwestern, Princeton and Wisconsin. 
</P>
<P>
 "I loved all the schools," she said. "But when i took the trip to Illinois, I 
had the feeling that it was the perfect place for me. I was most like the girls 
on the Illinois team. We just clicked." 
</P>
<P>
 Mehlman, a senior, had a 29-1 Mission League record this season. 
</P>
<P>
 She is rated 10th in the state and among the nation's top 50 players in the 
girls' 18-and-under division of the United States Tennis Assn. DAVE DESMOND 
</P>
