<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOORPARK PUTS A THIRD TITLE ON ITS SHELF WITH 26-21 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FERNANDO DOMINGUEZ, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three in a row. 
</P>
<P>
 That's what Moorpark College accomplished Saturday night with a 26-21 victory 
over Ventura in a Western State Conference football game at Ventura High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Raiders (7-2, 7-1 in WSC play) clinched at least a tie for their third 
consecutive North Division title. It was also the fourth consecutive victory 
for Moorpark, which is 4-0 in the division. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura (4-5, 3-4) dropped to 0-4 in the division. 
</P>
<P>
 Isaiah Mustafa, who had four catches for 64 yards, set a Moorpark 
single-season reception record. He has 56, one more than Dan Russell's 55 in 
1984. 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Damian Delfino completed nine of 23 passes for 220 yards and two 
touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark broke on top in the first quarter when Justin Simo intercepted a pass 
by Jason Brown and returned it 28 yards to give the Raiders a 7-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 The Raiders made it 9-0 when several players tackled Brown in the end zone for 
a safety. 
</P>
<P>
 After the free kick, Moorpark drove 57 yards to make it 16-0 when Delfino 
connected with Aaron Whitley on a 24-yard pass play. 
</P>
<P>
 The Raiders led, 23-0, at halftime on a 71-yard pass play from Delfino to 
Joaquin Evans. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura scored in the second half on David Simerly's 29-yard fumble return and 
two touchdown passes by reserve quarterback Aaron Triana -- the second coming 
with 1:01 left in the game. 
</P>
