<HEADLINE>
<P>
MASTER'S KNOCKED OUT IN NAIA FIRST ROUND; WOMEN'S VOLLEYBALL: SOUTHERN 
CALIFORNIA SWEEPS PAST THE MUSTANGS, 15-9, 15-12, 15-10. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE GALLUZZO, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Celeste Wright and Genevieve Young each had nine kills as Southern California 
College swept The Master's, 15-9, 15-12, 15-10, in a first-round volleyball 
match of the National Assn. of Intercollegiate Athletics Far West Regional. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was scared to death," said Vanguard Coach Eric Boyles, whose team defeated 
The Master's twice earlier in the season."It's usually a rule that you can't 
beat a team three times." 
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore Wendy Jones had 15 kills and Rose Dignadize added 22 assists for the 
fourth-seeded Mustangs (27-13). 
</P>
<P>
 Karajean Stephenson had four kills and 20 assists for fifth-seeded Southern 
California (18-10). 
</P>
<P>
 Master's was tentative early, committing eight service errors and four 
rotation errors in the first game. 
</P>
<P>
 "You play with more confidence when you are ahead," Master's Coach Dean Conk 
said. "But we were behind the whole time. We were playing not to lose and they 
were playing to win." 
</P>
<P>
 With the second game tied, 12-12, Vanguard Janine Katter served out the game. 
Southern California didn't trail again. 
</P>
</TEXT>
