<HEADLINE>
<P>
A LITTLE BIT OF HISTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cal State Northridge softball team, behind pitcher Kathy Slaten, defeated 
Akron in 1985 to win its third consecutive NCAA Division II title. 
</P>
<P>
 Slaten, a junior, was 41-11 and had 533 strikeouts in 410 1/3 innings. She 
finished her career the following season as a four-time Division II 
All-American and three-time Division II player of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 Slaten's career record at Northridge was 133-33-1 and she gave up only 41 
earned runs in 1,221 2/3 innings -- an 0.23 earned-run average In her 
Northridge career, she had 97 shutouts and 1,537 strikeouts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
