<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week:  
</P>
<P>
 * It's time to apply the first spray to combat peach leaf curl. 
</P>
<P>
 * A potful of planted bulbs can be started now and given at Christmas. 
</P>
<P>
 * Spring and summer flowering perennials to plant now are canterbury bells, 
candytuft, foxglove, columbine, cineraria and sweet william. 
</P>
<P>
 * Fall is the time to pay attention to thatch build-up in your lawn. Water 
does not penetrate well through thatch and insects love to use it as their 
home. Fall is also the best time to put in a new lawn. 
</P>
<P>
 * Check out the early blooming sasanqua camellias at your nursery today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
