<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIME TO MAKE DECEPTIVE LOAN DEALS ILLEGAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 What outraged me about the article headlined "Undisclosed Fees Spark Truth in 
Lending Battle" (Oct. 9) was that this loan shark was aware that Marta Rodash 
could not possibly afford to make the payments, not to mention the four points, 
but went ahead with the loan anyway. 
</P>
<P>
 I am disgusted that the only recourse the lawyer had was to go after them for 
not disclosing minuscule fees in the truth-in-lending disclosure, when in my 
mind, this is a clear case of fraud.I would like to see our government change 
the legislation to make such loan deals illegal. 
</P>
<P>
 People like Marta Rodash are all too susceptible to such rip-offs, and 
although the truth in lending law was set up to protect us by forcing lenders 
to disclose all fees, what use is it if the Marta Rodashes of the world cannot 
figure out that they are being ripped off until it is too late. 
</P>
<P>
 It is not enough and we have to do more to protect these people. 
</P>
<P>
 DEIRDRE KELLY 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine 
</P>
