<HEADLINE>
<P>
YOUTHS CAN WHISTLE WHILE THEY WORK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Basketball enthusiasts between 13 and 17 can learn to become certified 
basketball officials through a series of free classes sponsored by the city 
Department of Recreation and Parks. 
</P>
<P>
 Those who complete the course can become referees for youth basketball leagues 
at local recreation centers. 
</P>
<P>
 The class schedule is: 
</P>
<P>
 * Jan. 10 at the Costello Recreation Center, 3141 E. Olympic Blvd., (213) 
485-9111. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jan. 17 at the Eagle Rock Recreation Center, 1100 Eagle Vista Drive, (213) 
257-6948. 
</P>
<P>
 * Nov. 22 and Jan. 24 at the Echo Park Recreation Center, 1632 Bellevue Ave., 
(213) 250-3578. 
</P>
<P>
 Jan. 3 at the Normandie Recreation Center, 1550 S. Normandie Ave., (213) 
737-1181. 
</P>
</TEXT>
