<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTH: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; HOT LINE OFFERS LIST OF GOVERNMENT 
JOBS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles County has started a 24-hour job information hot line. 
</P>
<P>
 By dialing (213) 351-5478, job-seekers will have access to a listing of 
employment opportunities in county government. 
</P>
<P>
 The job list, which is updated weekly, features a two- to three-minute 
recorded message that allows callers to pick and choose job categories that 
meet their interests or qualifications. 
</P>
<P>
 Callers are connected to a menu of categories: clerical and administrative 
support, technical, engineering, crafts and maintenance, health care, public 
safety and the justice system. 
</P>
<P>
 The county's Department of Human Resources is providing the service with the 
assistance of Supervisor Yvonne Brathwaite Burke's office.  
</P>
<P>
 The computerized job bank refers callers to specific employers and aids them 
with other leads via telephone. 
</P>
