<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: MID-CITY AREA; JOB CORPS TO EXPLAIN ITS ROLE AT 
LUNCHEON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Mid-City Chamber of Commerce will hold its quarterly luncheon Thursday. 
Representatives from the YWCA/Los Angeles Job Corps will discuss how the 
program can help local businesses. 
</P>
<P>
 The Job Corps provides employers with youths ages 16 to 24 who have completed 
15 months of job training with hands-on experience. 
</P>
<P>
 The representatives will explain what the program costs participating 
businesses and how employers can qualify for tax credits. 
</P>
<P>
 Chamber members and other guests are asked to bring two canned or 
non-perishable food items to the meeting, which will go into the chamber's 
annual Thanksgiving donation to the needy. 
</P>
<P>
 The cost of the 12:30 luncheon is $12.50 per person. It will be at the Midtown 
Bowling Center, 4645 Venice Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 933-7171. 
</P>
