COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: PICO-UNION; FREE CITIZENSHIP CLASSES UNDERWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Citizenship classes sponsored by Belmont Community Adult School have begun at 
Angelica Lutheran Church, 1345 S. Burlington Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Held Tuesdays and Thursdays from 5 to 7:30 p.m., the classes are free and are 
taught in Spanish by bilingual staff. Enrollment is continuous, so there is no 
application deadline.  
</P>
